senses.sense_definition: Any tooth that is not a molar, such as an incisor, canine, or premolar.

examples.text: The dentist examined the <w>nonmolar</w> to see if it required a filling.
Human dentition includes molars for grinding and various types of <w>nonmolars</w> for biting and tearing.

senses.sense_definition: Describing a tooth or dental structure that is not a molar.

examples.text: The <w>nonmolar</w> teeth are located towards the front of the mouth.
He experienced sensitivity in the <w>nonmolar</w> region of his lower jaw.
